enemies are composed of different behavior types of encounters. 
The enemies carry the pieces that makes up the enemy, and categorized under behaviors
ideally, the difficulty goes up as behavior become smarter/more complicated

Violence: 
(naturally has average initiative roll)
    Cavalry charge
    infantry march
    Formation fighting
        
finesse: 
(naturally has higher initiative roll)
    archery ambush 
    hunting natives
    cavalry archer ambush
    Light cavalry charge

Defensive: 
(naturally has lower initiative roll)
    resting camp
    artillery holdout
    fortress

Bosses: 
    - act 1
    - act 2
    - act 3